The design of Fusio's compiler-compat layer (per-Kotlin-version CompatContext
implementations with ServiceLoader-based runtime selection and shaded artifact
distribution) is inspired by the `compiler-compat` module of ZacSweers/Metro:

  https://github.com/ZacSweers/metro

The same project also informed Fusio's gradle-plugin apply-time Kotlin
version warning: a single `supported-kotlin-versions.txt` source-of-truth
file is read at build time, baked as a resource, and consulted at apply
time to warn the consumer when their Kotlin compiler sits outside the
tested range. The pattern is adopted; the implementation is independent.

Metro is Copyright Zac Sweers and contributors, and is distributed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0.

No source code from Metro is incorporated into Fusio; only the architectural
patterns are adopted. This notice exists to acknowledge that intellectual debt.
